<subSubSection id="FAAF65449710FFD3FF1F291BBD2DA1A5" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B20A36CF9710FFD3FF1F291BBB33A17C" blockId="5.[151,1437,1618,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FF1F291BB86FA030" bold="true" box="[151,267,1618,1644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the most important characters of this species are the presence of dense metatergal setation, and of adenostyles only on male femora 2, coupled with the gonofemorite being quite slender and long, but with clear evidence of torsion, while the solenophore is also peculiar in shape and rather similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FB5429D2BC1BA0E8" baseAuthorityName="Carl" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[1244,1407,1691,1716]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asperrimum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FB5429D2BC1BA0E8" box="[1244,1407,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. asperrimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: a large, rounded, mesal lobe (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FE5829F7B88BA084" bold="true" box="[464,495,1726,1752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo)</emphasis>
, but only a single apicolateral spine (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FC1C29F7BAC6A084" bold="true" box="[916,930,1726,1752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">a</emphasis>
) distal to the basal loop of a free solenomere (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FF2929ABB9D0A0A0" bold="true" box="[161,180,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
). Base of 
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FEA329ABB825A0A0" bold="true" box="[299,321,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo</emphasis>
on mesal side forming a protecting shield for the basal 
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FC4A29ABBAB1A0A0" bold="true" box="[962,981,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
loop. Distal half of solenophore clearly curved and directed laterad (
<figureCitation id="2A8E2A4A9710FFD3FE5E284FBB2FA17C" box="[470,587,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1167,1191]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,188,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1436,181,1143]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Polydrepanum horridum Golovatch, 1984. Right gonopod, lateral, dorsal, mesal and ventral views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, apicolateral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, mesal lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709518/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B20A36CF9710FFD3FF4F2863BD2DA1A5" blockId="5.[151,1437,1618,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
Despite some critical comments following the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FC5E2862BD38A118" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" box="[982,1116,1834,1860]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FC5E2862BD38A118" box="[982,1116,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bano, 1997, 1998; 
<bibRefCitation id="D6244B3E9710FFD3FACC2862B857A134" author="Bano, K. &amp; Murthy, J. B." pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="155 - 162" refId="ref13259" refString="Bano, K. &amp; Murthy, J. B. (1997) Gonopods of some South Indian paradoxosomatid millipedes (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Entomologica Scandinavica, Supplement 51, 155 - 162." type="journal article" year="1997">Bano &amp; Murthy, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D6244B3E9710FFD3FEB62806BB0CA134" author="Nguyen, A. D. &amp; Sierwald, P." box="[318,616,1870,1897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="1132 - 1353" refId="ref15022" refString="Nguyen, A. D. &amp; Sierwald, P. (2013) A worldwide catalog of the family Paradoxosomatidae Daday, 1889 (Diplopoda: Polydesmida). Check List, 9 (6), 1132 - 1353. [https: // www. researchgate. net / publication / 261875647 _ A _ worldwide _ catalog _ of _ the _ family _ Paradoxosomatidae _ Daday _ 1889 _ Diplopoda _ Polydesmida] https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 9.6.1132" type="journal article" year="2013">Nguyen &amp; Sierwald, 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D6244B3E9710FFD3FDFC2807BAD7A135" author="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wesener, T." box="[628,947,1870,1897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="1" refId="ref14314" refString="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wesener, T. (2016) A species checklist of the millipedes (Myriapoda, Diplopoda) of India. Zootaxa, 4129 (1), 001 - 075. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4129.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Golovatch &amp; Wesener, 2016</bibRefCitation>
) that suggested the erection of a new genus to accommodate this species alone, we still feel that the distinctions are not strong enough to do so, because both 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FA00283AB865A1EC" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FA00283AB865A1EC" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FEBD28DEB8C8A1EC" authorityName="Carl" authorityYear="1932" box="[309,428,1942,1968]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamilum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FEBD28DEB8C8A1EC" box="[309,428,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. tamilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation id="2A8E2A4A9710FFD3FE5528DFBB28A1EC" box="[477,588,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1167,1191]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,188,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1436,181,1143]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Polydrepanum horridum Golovatch, 1984. Right gonopod, lateral, dorsal, mesal and ventral views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, apicolateral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, mesal lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709518/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="2A8E2A4A9710FFD3FD0828DFBBA3A1EC" box="[640,711,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1796]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,1008,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-321@8.[151,1437,1002,1749]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–20. Polydrepanum tamilum Carl, 1932. 16. Male leg 2, lateral view. 17. Entire left gonopod, mesal view. 18. Distal half of left gonopod, lateral view. 19. Entire right gonopod, mesal view. 20. Distal half of right gonopod, sublateral view. 16–18: after Carl (1932); 19, 20: after Jeekel (1980b). Abbreviations: a and b, dorsal distofemoral processes; ad, adenostyle; lo, lateral protecting lobe/shield; k, basal loop of solenomere; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Drawn not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">17–19</figureCitation>
) share such decisive characters as a twisted gonofemorite and the basal loop of a flagelliform solenomere (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FDEA28F3BB11A188" bold="true" box="[610,629,1978,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
) protected by a large lobe (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FC2328F3BAAEA188" bold="true" box="[939,970,1978,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo)</emphasis>
of a distally strongly curved solenophore (
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FF292897B9AFA1A4" bold="true" box="[161,203,2014,2040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sph</emphasis>
). In other words, we consider 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FDA92896BBC2A1A4" authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" box="[545,678,2014,2040]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FDA92896BBC2A1A4" box="[545,678,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="75B54D4C9710FFD3FC432896BD27A1A4" authorityName="Carl" authorityYear="1932" box="[971,1091,2014,2040]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamilum">
<emphasis id="80C1EADD9710FFD3FC432896BD27A1A4" box="[971,1091,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. tamilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
